## 4. Lemma 2: Kernel-bank mixture sensitivity decomposition

For each edge descriptor $z$, define:

- the kernel-bank response vector:
  $$
  \kappa(z) = [\kappa_1(z), \ldots, \kappa_M(z)]
  $$
- the coefficient map:
  $$
  \alpha(z)
  $$
- the scalar interaction map:
  $$
  \phi_\theta(z) = \langle \alpha(z), \kappa(z) \rangle
  $$

Assume that on $\mathcal U$:

- each primitive is bounded and locally Lipschitz:
  $$
  |\kappa_m(z)| \le B_{\kappa_m}
  $$
  $$
  |\kappa_m(z) - \kappa_m(z')| \le L_{\kappa_m}\|z - z'\|
  $$

- the coefficient map is bounded in $\ell_1$:
  $$
  \|\alpha(z)\|_1 \le A
  $$

- the coefficient map is locally Lipschitz in $\ell_1$:
  $$
  \|\alpha(z) - \alpha(z')\|_1 \le L_\alpha \|z - z'\|
  $$

Define
$$
B_\kappa := \max_m B_{\kappa_m}, \qquad
L_\kappa := \max_m L_{\kappa_m}.
$$

### Lemma 2

Under the assumptions above, the scalar interaction map $\phi_\theta(z)$ is locally Lipschitz in descriptor space, with
$$
|\phi_\theta(z) - \phi_\theta(z')|
\le
\big(A L_\kappa + B_\kappa L_\alpha\big)\|z - z'\|.
$$

Equivalently, letting
$$
L_{\mathrm{bank}} := A L_\kappa, \qquad
L_{\mathrm{mix}} := B_\kappa L_\alpha,
$$
we have
$$
L_\phi \le L_{\mathrm{bank}} + L_{\mathrm{mix}}.
$$

### Proof

For any $z, z'$,
$$
\phi_\theta(z) - \phi_\theta(z')
=
\langle \alpha(z), \kappa(z) - \kappa(z') \rangle
+
\langle \alpha(z) - \alpha(z'), \kappa(z') \rangle.
$$

Taking absolute values and applying Hölder’s inequality in $(\ell_1,\ell_\infty)$ gives
$$
|\phi_\theta(z) - \phi_\theta(z')|
\le
\|\alpha(z)\|_1 \|\label{\kappa}(z) - \kappa(z')\|_\infty
+
\|\alpha(z) - \alpha(z')\|_1 \|\kappa(z')\|_\infty.
$$

By the assumptions,
$$
\|\alpha(z)\|_1 \le A,
\qquad
\|\kappa(z) - \kappa(z')\|_\infty \le L_\kappa \|z - z'\|,
$$
$$
\|\alpha(z) - \alpha(z')\|_1 \le L_\alpha \|z - z'\|,
\qquad
\|\kappa(z')\|_\infty \le B_\kappa.
$$

Substituting gives
$$
|\phi_\theta(z) - \phi_\theta(z')|
\le
\big(A L_\kappa + B_\kappa L_\alpha\big)\|z - z'\|,
$$
which proves the claim.

### Remark

This is the same bank/mixing decomposition used in Eq. (9) of the main paper and Eq. (20) of Appendix C.1; the point here is only to restate it as a standalone lemma.

